club_events.description:
A brief description of the talk given by Dr. Josh Nahum:

Haskell (one of the best examples of design by committee) is certainly the most beautiful programming languages ever designed. And just like how you can write terrible Java code in any language, Haskell will elevate your senses and you'll see the world in a new light. It combines a strict, purely functional language with a clean, crisp syntax which allows you to solve problems in an entirely new manner. During this talk, I'll teach the basics of the language and provide resources for learning more. I'm trying to free your mind, Neo. But I can only show you the door. You're the one that has to walk through it.
club_events.name: Haskell: An Elegant Weapon for a More Civilized Age

club_events.description:
This talk will be held in room 1145 in the Engineering Building

Dr. Ross will be giving this talk.
Here is a brief description of what the talk will encompasss.


Biometrics is the science of recognizing individuals based on their physical and behavioral attributes such as fingerprints, face, iris, voice and signature. The automated process of comparing a pair of biometric signals (such as two face images) and determining whether they belong to the same individual or not is both a fascination as well as a practical area of research. Biometric solutions have been incorporated in smartphones, laptops, border security systems, criminal investigations, time-and-attendance technology and national ID cards. This Talk will discuss the recent progress made in biometrics and enumerate some of ther cutting edge problems being addressed by researchers in this field.
club_events.name: On Faces and Fingerprints: Human Recognition Using Biometrics

club_events.description:
Come out and join us for our first game jam of the semester!  Completely free, no materials required! (Though a laptop is recommended).

FAQ's:

"What is a game jam?"

A game jam is an event where you (and a team) will make a small game in a short period of time (just 48 hours!). You will be given a theme, and you will use this theme to get started with your idea. At the end of the weekend, we will be showing off your games to the rest of the club!

"Can I pick my own team?"

Of course! We will be happy to help people who are new to the club find teams as well.

"Do I have to stay and make my game through the entire weekend? Can I go home and sleep?"

Although some people choose to go hard and jam the entire weekend, there is no obligation to stay there all the time. Feel free to go home and get some sleep if you're feeling beat!

"What if I don't know Unity very well?"

Not a problem! All of our officers will be on hand to help you with any issues you might have. We are here to make sure you can make cool games!

"What if I have an event that causes me to miss one of the days?"

Feel free to come whenever you can! Game Jams are a time to have fun, not worry about commitment issues. Stop by whenever you can and stay for as long as you're able!
club_events.name: Fall Semester Game Jam!
